result.execSummary:
The defendant Cornell McKinnie was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Cornell McKinnie is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Cornell McKinnie was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court with attorney Julius Andriusis.  Paul L. Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements to the court by state, defense, defendant.
Additional statement by Bridget F.
Prior to sentence being imposed Ms. F. exited the courtroom.
Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction; credit for 1 day served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 1 YEAR with the following conditions:
-Follow all rules of probation.
-No further violations of the law.
-No contact with the victim, B.F.
-Counseling needs to be determined: domestic violence and/or anger management.
-Perform 25 HOURS of community service at a non-profit agency.
-Pay victim witness surcharge and all costs, assessments and surcharges.
-Submit DNA sample and pay related costs.
-Pay stipulated restitution in the amount of $766.87 to victim, B.F.
Failure to pay all costs, assessments and surcharges and restitution will result in civil judgment.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court with attorney Julius Andriusis.  Paul L. Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case is spun for trial from Branch 25.
Jury panel in court.  Voir dire proceeded at the hour of  11:15am.  
Thirteen (13) good and lawful citizens of the County of Milwaukee, WI qualified to serve as jurors in the above entitled cause were duly impanelled.  Jury list received and filed.  Court recessed for lunch.  Jurors and parties to return at 1:15pm.
Case called at 1:25pm.  All parties are present in court.  Jury in the box and sworn. Court instructed jury.  Opening statements by state and defense.  Trial proceeded.  Sworn for the state:  Bridget F.  Jury out of box at 2:35pm.  Jury in the box at 2:45pm.  Sworn for the state:  PO Barbara Court(MPD).  Exhibits 1 and 2 received.  State rests subject to rebuttal.  Jury out of the box at 3pm.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and DENIED.  Colloquy between the court and defendant as to his decision to testify in his own behalf.
Defendant now wishes to resolve this matter.  State is in agreement with resolution.
As to count 2, BATTERY:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  
As to counts 1 and 3, counts are ordered dismissed.  Sentencing to be adjourned as victim has left the building and must be notified.
Case is adjourned to 12-18-2014 at 8:15 for sentencing.
Exhibits are withdrawn and returned to the state.
Branch 25 in trial and unable to hear this matter today. Branch 38 agreed to hear this matter for Branch 25. Parties notified. Deputy Court Clerk ccp.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court with attorney Julius Andriusis.  Paul L. Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for jury trial. Parties are prepared to proceed. Branch 25 in trial and will attempt to locate a spin court for this case. Discussion regarding number of witnesses in this case and the anticipated length of the trial. Case passed to locate spin court.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court with attorney Julius Andriusis.  Paul L. Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for final pretrial. Parties are prepared to proceed to trial and are still in negotiations. Both parties have filed their pretrial documents. State placed offer on the record. Case remains scheduled for jury trial on 12/03/14. Case adjourned to Branch 25.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court with attorney Julius Andriusis.  Paul L. Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for jury trial. Attorney Andriusis has been retained in this matter. Branch 25 has a speedy trial and a homicide trial scheduled and is unable to hear this matter today. Court ordered this matter adjourned. Case adjourned to Branch 25.  Final pre-trial scheduled for November 24, 2014 at 01:30 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for December 3, 2014 at 10:00 am.
Received and filed:  Original Transcript of PRELIMINARY HEARING Proceedings commencing 6-3-2014  (20 pages) and Certification of Filing Transcript.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court pro se.  Paul L. Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for final pretrial. Defendant may be hiring attorney Julius Andriusis to act as a standby counsel during the jury trial. Defendant did not give the Court any other potential attorneys he is talking to. Any motions to be filed by 8/29/14. Parties to file witness lists, motions in limine and jury instructions by the final pretrial date. Case remains scheduled for jury trial on 10/27/2014. Case adjourned to Branch 25.
State's Requested Jury Instructions with substantive instructions received and filed. Deputy Court Clerk ccp.
State's Witness List received and filed. Deputy Court Clerk ccp.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court.  Paul L. Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for scheduling conference. State has turned over all discovery and an offer to the defendant. Court held colloquy with the defendant to determine if he still wishes to proceed pro se. Defendant requests additional time to consider hiring a private attorney. Defendant raised concerns he does not have all discovery. Court recommended the defendant write a letter to the State with any discovery he believes is missing. Court ordered this matter scheduled for final pretrial and jury trial. Case adjourned to Branch 25.  Final pre-trial scheduled for August 07, 2014 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for October 27, 2014 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court.  Paul L Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for arraignment. Defendant wishes to continue pro se. State turned over discovery and an offer to the defendant. Discussion regarding contents of discovery. Original Information filed.  Copy given to defendant. Court formally read the charges and maximum penalties to the defendant. Defendant plead not guilty to all counts. Defendant requested additional time to review the discovery. Case adjourned to Branch 25.  Scheduling conference scheduled for July 10, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court.  Paul L Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Court reviews with the defendant the WAIVER OF RIGHT TO ATTORNEY form signed on May 15, 2014.  Court finds that the Defendant freely and knowingly wishes to proceed pro se for the Preliminary Hearing. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the state:B.F.  State rests.  Defendant rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Case is scheduled for an Arraignment on June 18, 2014 at 8:30 a.m.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court.  Paul L Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for indigency hearing. Defendant wishes to proceed pro se. Defendant sworn in. Court held colloquy with defendant. Case passed to address court calendar and allow defendant to fill out the waiver of attorney form. 
Case recalled. Miriam Falk appeared on behalf of Paul Tiffin for the State of Wisconsin. All other appearances remain the same. Defendant has filled out the Waiver of Attorney form which was received and filed. Court reviewed the form with the defendant. Court read charges and maximum penalties to the defendant. Court finds the defendant knowingly and intelligently elects to proceed pro se. Case adjourned to Branch PE.

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court.  Danielle Chojnacki for Paul L Tiffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant appears without counsel.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Rothstein, Branch 25.   Court suspends the proceedings and orders the case adjourned for CAUSE for an Indigency Hearing.  Same Bail. 
  Indigency hearing scheduled for May 15, 2014 at 08:30 am.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order. Defendant is to have no contact with B.F. (d.o.b. 10-14-1961).   mld

Defendant Cornell McKinnie in court with attorney Julius Andriusis.  Kristin M Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defense moves for dismissal without argument.  Court heard and denied defense motion to dismiss.  Defendant pled not guilty to misdemeanor count #2.  Attorney Andriusus has not been officially appointed to case 2014CF1691.  Court ordered case adjourned for Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Court on 5-8-2014 at 8:30 am.
